# Specs to skip during e2e generation.
# One path per line (relative to specs root). Lines starting with # are comments.

# ============================================================
# AZURE DATA PLANE SPECS — Triage (task 20.6, 2026-03-07)
# ============================================================
# All 32 Azure data plane specs emit successfully with flavor=azure.
# However, ALL 32 specs fail to build under net8.0 TFM (1904 CS errors).
# They build fine under netstandard2.0. Test files are linked from the
# legacy submodule (task 20.5) but Azure tests don't run because
# SpectorTestAttribute silently skips them.
#
# Root cause: Generated infrastructure files (ClientPipelineExtensions.cs,
# ErrorResult.cs, RestClient.cs) use wrong API surface under net8.0:
#   - CS0246: HttpMessage type not found (should be PipelineMessage)
#   - CS1501: CreateMessage(Uri, string, Classifier) — wrong overload
#   - CS1061: RequestHeaders.Set, HttpMessage.Apply — methods don't exist
#   - CS1729: Response<T> 2-arg constructor doesn't exist
#   - CS1061: RequestContext.Parse() doesn't exist
#   - CS1503: RequestContext → CancellationToken, BinaryContent → RequestContent
#
# These are NOT in .testignore — specs are still generated to preserve
# visibility into emitter changes. The net8.0 build errors are pre-existing
# (also affect 10 non-Azure specs with identical error patterns).
#
# --- azure/client-generator-core (15 specs) — emits ✅, net8.0 build ❌ ---
# access, alternate-type, api-version/{header,path,query},
# client-default-value, client-initialization/{default,individually,individuallyParent},
# client-location/{move-method-parameter-to-client,move-to-existing-sub-client,
#   move-to-new-sub-client,move-to-root-client},
# deserialize-empty-string-as-null, flatten-property, hierarchy-building,
# next-link-verb, override, usage
#
# --- azure/core (7 specs) — emits ✅, net8.0 build ❌ ---
# basic, lro/rpc, lro/standard, model, page, scalar, traits
#
# --- azure/encode (1), azure/example (1), azure/payload (1) — emits ✅, net8.0 build ❌ ---
# --- azure/special-headers (1), azure/versioning/previewVersion (v1/v2) — emits ✅, net8.0 build ❌ ---
#
# Total: 32 Azure data plane specs emit (0 emit failures)
# Total: 32 Azure data plane specs fail net8.0 build (1904 CS errors)
# Total: 27 Azure test files linked (none run — SpectorTestAttribute skips)
# Total non-Azure net8.0 build failures: 10 specs (584 CS errors, same patterns)

# ============================================================
# NON-AZURE SPECS — ignored
# ============================================================

# === Multipart / file upload specs ===
# type/file: Convenience methods reference File model types via refkeys, but
# these file models don't have JSON/XML usage and are filtered from generation.
# File download operations need special handling to return BinaryData/stream
# instead of model types in convenience methods.
type/file

# === Multi-namespace scope issues ===
# Internal infrastructure types (ClientUriBuilder, Argument, extension methods)
# are generated in one namespace but referenced from sub-clients in a different
# namespace. Individual project builds succeed; fails in combined E2E build.
service/multi-service
client/structure/client-operation-group
